message: >-
  If you use these patterns in your systems, research, or publications,
  please cite this repository using the metadata below.
type: software
title: >-
  finserv-agent-audit: Governance Patterns for Autonomous AI
  Agents in Regulated Financial Services
authors:
  - family-names: Bhaduri
    given-names: Kunjar
    orcid: ""
    affiliation: North Texas Capital Investments
    website: "https://linkedin.com/in/kunjarbhaduri"
repository-code: "https://github.com/linus10x/finserv-agent-audit"
url: "https://github.com/linus10x/finserv-agent-audit"
abstract: >-
  Reference governance patterns, schemas, agents, and runnable
  implementations for audit-ready autonomous AI agents in regulated
  financial services. Covers autonomy-level classification (A0 through
  A4) — a proprietary governance framework documented in this repository
  — along with DEFCON-style risk-state degradation, sovereign veto
  architecture, shadow-mode rollout, tamper-detecting hash-chain audit
  logging (within-trust-boundary), four Protocol seams for audit-chain
  integrity (LedgerStore, TimestampSource, WitnessRegister, MIProxy),
  VendorScoreGate for third-party AI scoring drift detection, and the
  FSI-specific governance gates (ModelInventory for SR 11-7,
  AdverseActionGate for FCRA + CFPB Circular 2022-03, SARWorkflowAudit
  for BSA/AML, EquityAudit for ECOA/Reg B, BestInterestCheck for SEC
  Reg-BI, ProtectedClassProxyDetector mutual-information arm). v1.3
  added seven governance modules covering the discrimination frontier
  and third-party vendor surface (LDASearchHarness,
  LLMDisparateImpactHarness, EffectiveChallengeHarness,
  VendorAttestationLedger, RetrainingCadenceMonitor, DeprecationWatch,
  CustomerFacingChatbotGuardrail), the foundation-model API
  vendor-clauses (sixth vendor class), and six regulatory + incident +
  disclosure docs. v2.0 ships the agentic-AI ecosystem and platform
  surfaces: four agentic-runtime audit adapters (Google A2A, LangGraph,
  Microsoft Agent Framework, CrewAI), an AIBOMGenerator producing
  CycloneDX 1.7 ML-BOM + SPDX 3.0 AI Profile artifacts from a single
  governance state, a FastAPI governance endpoint with OpenAPI 3.1 + a
  Server-Sent Events live stream, a Kubernetes operator stub with three
  custom resource definitions (AuditChain, SovereignVeto, ChainSink)
  alongside Kyverno and OPA sample admission policies, and an
  adversarial test pack combining Garak probes, Promptfoo scenarios,
  and a Python harness per the ADR-0018 threat model. v2.0 also adds
  five strategic docs (NAIC Model Bulletin on the Use of AI Systems by
  Insurers, DORA mapping, EU AI Act August 2026 compliance pack, PE
  portfolio playbook, PCAOB AS 2201 amendments ASSURANCE-GUIDE
  appendix) plus eight new ADRs (0027-0034). Maps to twenty-plus
  regulatory frameworks including SR 11-7, OCC 2011-12 (historical) +
  OCC 2026-13 overlay, GLBA, FCRA, ECOA, BSA/AML, SOX 404 ITGC, SEC
  17a-4, SEC Reg-BI, CFPB Circular 2022-03, CFPB Circular 2023-09,
  NYDFS Part 500, NAIC Model Bulletin on the Use of AI Systems by
  Insurers, NIST AI RMF, NIST AI 600-1 GenAI Profile, Treasury FS AI
  RMF, ISO/IEC 42001, COSO ICAIR, EU AI Act 2024/1689, DORA
  (Regulation (EU) 2022/2554), PCAOB AS 2201 amendments, and multiple
  state-AG AI enforcement matters. Patterns were extracted from a
  multi-year private quantitative options research program with Marcos
  López de Prado as named advisor on adjacent work; the source program
  operates in paper-trading Phase 0 — no live capital has been deployed.
keywords:
  - AI governance
  - autonomous agents
  - financial services
  - EU AI Act
  - regulated AI
  - human-in-the-loop
  - audit trail
  - fintech
  - multi-agent systems
  - compliance
